List security groups exposing port 8080 to the internet:

aws ec2 describe-security-groups \
--query "SecurityGroups[*].IpPermissions[?FromPort==`8080` && IpRanges[?CidrIp=='0.0.0.0/0']]"
Check IPv6 exposure
aws ec2 describe-security-groups \
--query "SecurityGroups[*].IpPermissions[?FromPort==`8080` && Ipv6Ranges[?CidrIpv6=='::/0']]"
Better CLI command (shows SG ID)
aws ec2 describe-security-groups \
--query "SecurityGroups[*].{SG:GroupId,Rules:IpPermissions[?FromPort==`8080`]}"
